libwave copyright/license information:

The original, IrisGL version of libwave was written circa 1992 by
Dave Pape, while a federal government employee at NASA.  That work
has no copyright.

Revisions, including the OpenGL interface, were written in 1995-1996
by Dave Pape, while a graduate student at the University of Illinois
at Chicago.  This code is released under an "MIT license", as follows:


